FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
**!!!POSSIBLE BREAKING CHANGE!!!** * Moved all of the enumerations out of the Hex.Html namespace and into the Hex namespace.
Changes: * Changed Step to accept object parameter. * Changed Step to support passing in TimeFormat to determine correct step value.
Enhancements: * Added support for specifying attributes in a strongly-typed fluent way for all existing AjaxHelper methods. * Added support for specifying attributes on any Html element with Html.Attributes extension method. * Added BeginActionLink, BeginRouteLink and EndLink to HtmlHelper and AjaxHelper to allow any nested content instead of just text.

FeedPackage.Description: Extensions to HtmlHelper for things like checkbox lists, adds support for most to HTML5 input types and provides a fluent strongly-type way of specifying attributes.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
**!!!POSSIBLE BREAKING CHANGE!!!** * Changed how a list of checkboxes are created. Instead of overloads to the CheckBoxFor method, there are new methods on the HtmlHelper called CheckBoxListItem and CheckBoxListItemFor. If you are currently using Version 2.2.0, this will cause a breaking change.
Enhancements: * Added overloads to CheckBox and CheckBoxFor to create a checkbox with values for checked and unchecked other than the default true/false. * Added better support for creating a list of checkboxes by using the methods CheckBoxListItem and CheckBoxListItemFor. * Added methods Description and DescriptionFor to retrieve the description value specified in the view model with the DataAnnotation attributes. * Added support for removing a class that you previously specified in your attribute expression.
FeedPackage.Summary: Extensions to HtmlHelper for things like checkbox lists, adds support for most to HTML5 input types and provides a fluent strongly-type way of specifying attributes.
FeedPackage.Tags: Asp.Net MVC HtmlHelper Extensions HTML5 CheckBoxList CheckBox List
FeedPackage.Title: Hex

FeedPackage.Description: Extensions to HtmlHelper for things like checkbox lists, adds support for most to HTML5 input types and provides a fluent strongly-type way of specifying attributes.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Enhancements: * Added support for input type="submit" by using the methods SubmitInputButton and SubmitInputButtonFor. * Add support for the button element by using the methods Button and ButtonFor for button type="button" and SubmitButton and SubmitButtonFor for button type="submit". * Also added BeginButton, BeginButtonFor, BeginSubmitButton and BeginSubmitButtonFor to allow you to specify html content as the value of the button. * Added CheckBoxListItemLabel and CheckBoxListItemLabelFor for creating labels for checkboxes created with CheckBoxListItem and CheckBoxListItemFor.

FeedPackage.Description: Using Windows Forms or Windows WPF SendKey methods can emulate text entry, but not actual key strokes. Other available input simulators or emulators lack ability to send key strokes that is behind DirectX layers, and rarely provides output features as one package. HenoohDeviceEmulator provides easy way to gain hardware access to Keyboard and Mouse devices, both input and output. Henooh Device Emulator is composed of four separate classes each designed to handle their own functionality.
FeedPackage.Summary: HenoohDeviceEmulator provides a simple .NET (C#) interface to emulate Keyboard and Mouse input and output. Input classes are called Controllers and Output classes are called Observers.
FeedPackage.Tags: Henooh Input Simualator Emulator Keyboard Mouse Control

FeedPackage.Description:
A small Silverlight Glimpse window sits on top of your Silverlight application displaying real time error counts for bindings, validations and exceptions as your application hits its bugs. To view the detail of each individual error just click the expand button on the window to show all the relevant information.
This debugging tool is written in C# and compiles to a dll which can be referenced from your Silverlight application. You will also need to reference the System.Windows.Controls.Dll (part of the Silverlight Toolkit SDK).
FeedPackage.Summary: Silverlight Glimpse helps developers track down binding errors, highlight validation errors and unhandled exceptions in their application.
FeedPackage.Title: SilverlightGlimpse
